 "text": "\n\nFix: \n\n\u003cvuxml xmlns=\"http://www.vuxml.org/apps/vuxml-1\"\u003e\n   \u003cvuln vid=\"27c0b5c2-4d98-47ca-929f-c61f507af137\"\u003e\n     \u003ctopic\u003epy-pycrypto -- PyCrypto ARC2 Module Buffer Overflow\u003c/topic\u003e\n     \u003caffects\u003e\n       \u003cpackage\u003e\n         \u003cname\u003epy-pycrypto\u003c/name\u003e\n         \u003crange\u003e\u003cle\u003e2.0.1_1\u003c/le\u003e\u003c/range\u003e\n       \u003c/package\u003e\n     \u003c/affects\u003e\n     \u003cdescription\u003e\n       \u003cbody xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\u003e\n         \u003cp\u003eSANS reports:\u003c/p\u003e\n         \u003cblockquote cite=\"http://gitweb2.dlitz.net/?p=crypto/pycrypto-2.x.gita=commitdiffh=d1c4875e1f220652fe7ff8358f56dee3b2aba31b\"\u003e\n           \u003cp\u003ePyCrypto is exposed to a buffer overflow issue because it fails to adequately verify user-supplied input. This issue resides in the ARC2 module. This issue can be triggered with specially crafted ARC2 keys in excess of 128 bytes.\u003c/p\u003e\n         \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n       \u003c/body\u003e\n     \u003c/description\u003e\n     \u003creferences\u003e\n      \u003curl\u003ehttp://gitweb2.dlitz.net/?p=crypto/pycrypto-2.x.gita=commitdiffh=d1c4875e1f220652fe7ff8358f56dee3b2aba31b\u003c/url\u003e\n     \u003c/references\u003e\n     \u003cdates\u003e\n       \u003cdiscovery\u003e2009-02-06\u003c/discovery\u003e\n       \u003centry\u003e2009-02-14\u003c/entry\u003e\n     \u003c/dates\u003e\n   \u003c/vuln\u003e"
}